This is the Science Fiction Radio Show, a commentary on science fiction and fantasy.

24:00.040 --> 24:01.780
And here are your hosts.

24:06.320 --> 24:07.640
This is David Crews.

24:07.900 --> 24:08.520
And Daryl Lane.

24:09.040 --> 24:13.860
Jack Chalker's reputation was greatly enhanced by the popular Well World series of novels.

24:14.220 --> 24:19.300
Now he's at work on a new series, one which will have four books in it, entitled The Four Lords of the Diamond.

24:19.800 --> 24:24.820
Two novels have been published so far. The first is called Lilith, and the second Cerberus.

24:25.500 --> 24:27.000
Chalker comments on the story.

24:28.700 --> 24:34.500
It has a tremendous number of the elements that I have become known for.

24:34.500 --> 24:38.640
It has a lot of new material as well. It has a lot of political commentary.

24:39.220 --> 24:41.420
It has a lot of social commentary in it.

24:41.660 --> 24:47.140
It has also slam-bang action, Machiavellian intrigue, and everything else,

24:47.180 --> 24:50.820
because nobody's going to read your message if you don't entertain first.

24:52.260 --> 24:55.100
As Chalker says, the books have a lot of excitement in them.

24:55.280 --> 24:58.000
In the opening pages of Lilith, the first book in the series,

24:58.260 --> 25:03.240
a tremendously powerful alien robot penetrates a top-secret military installation on Earth.

25:03.400 --> 25:08.160
The robot's discovered, but he escapes and heads for a planetary system called the Warden Diamond.

25:08.160 --> 25:10.380
The Earth government sends its top agent.

25:12.220 --> 25:18.740
These are four worlds in one system that are basically a prison planet series,

25:18.740 --> 25:22.100
and you get dropped on there.

25:22.520 --> 25:27.020
And the foundation idea, which appeals to me an awful lot,

25:27.200 --> 25:31.500
is an alien race discovers us before we discover them,

25:32.440 --> 25:35.940
decides that it can't win a war against us.

25:35.940 --> 25:39.660
Maybe there's just not as many of them,

25:39.700 --> 25:43.480
or there's technological problems, or something like that.

25:43.980 --> 25:45.880
So they study us and study us,

25:45.940 --> 25:50.220
and they discover that, as in all human societies,

25:50.220 --> 25:52.100
there is this massive criminal syndicate,

25:53.120 --> 25:56.260
and that this criminal syndicate,

25:57.600 --> 26:04.120
leaders are mostly imprisoned for life on the four lords of the diamond,

26:04.120 --> 26:06.660
the Warden Diamond, these four worlds.

26:06.980 --> 26:15.000
So what the aliens do is they contact these bitter super crooks,

26:15.620 --> 26:18.040
and they take out a contract on human civilization.

26:19.760 --> 26:23.260
The agent can't land on any of the four worlds of the Warden Diamond.

26:23.560 --> 26:28.040
A tiny organism on these worlds enters the body and makes a person a virtual prisoner.

26:28.300 --> 26:28.760
Right.

26:28.980 --> 26:31.040
If you try to leave, you die a painful death.

26:31.220 --> 26:33.000
There seems to be no cure for it either.

26:33.000 --> 26:37.980
So what the agent does is have his personality implanted into four separate bodies,

26:37.980 --> 26:40.420
and these bodies are sent to each of the worlds.

26:40.600 --> 26:44.480
And he monitors what is happening through a computer hookup orbiting the Warden system.

26:45.480 --> 26:53.440
Part of what the book is about is that we have a sort of surrogate hymn down on each of these worlds,

26:54.560 --> 26:58.160
who starts off pretty much almost identical to him.

26:58.960 --> 27:04.080
And he's following this whole thing with his whole system of values, beliefs, and so on.

27:04.080 --> 27:09.920
And he's watching the surrogates change into quite different people.

27:10.840 --> 27:16.500
And it begins to eat away at his own sense of values, his own sense of duty.

27:17.160 --> 27:27.620
As a matter of fact, in the third book, he begins to realize that the people who sent him there on this mission anticipated this.

27:28.140 --> 27:35.240
And that his computer detective aide, who he has dialogues with and discusses everything with,

27:35.640 --> 27:36.740
may be more than that.

27:36.900 --> 27:38.520
It may be something of a watchdog.

27:40.640 --> 27:45.320
Chalker promises an exciting ending when the agent struggles with his own newly discovered values,

27:45.320 --> 27:47.500
with the computer, and with the aliens.

27:49.220 --> 27:50.720
I don't like cop-outs.

27:50.880 --> 27:53.460
I don't like stringing people along and then not delivering.

27:53.920 --> 28:02.380
So you will get real, I don't know whether you can say flesh and blood, but something, aliens,

28:03.760 --> 28:05.340
and whatever they're made of.

28:06.280 --> 28:11.060
You will meet the aliens, you will have a face down,

28:11.080 --> 28:16.740
and the solution to the whole thing and exactly what's going on is quite bizarre.

28:17.000 --> 28:18.580
And I don't think anybody's going to figure it out.

